parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the all-wheel drive system can cause loss of power, reduced traction, and handling issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning message "All Wheel Drive System Problem
Only Front Wheels May Be Powered. See Dealer"

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of various electric systems, including ABS, electric power steering, collision mitigation, and others, can cause loss of control, reduced safety features, and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the wheel speed sensor can cause various electric systems to malfunction, leading to loss of control, reduced safety features, and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the Engine Control Unit (ECU) can cause loss of power, reduced control, and safety issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the 360 surround camera system can cause reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Camera system not showing a 360-degree view
blind spots or stitching lines in the camera display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wireless phone charger can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving.
symptoms: Wireless phone charger stops working after a short period of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple warning lights to appear on the dashboard, leading to a loss of critical safety features, reduced performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights on the dashboard
and various risk mitigation systems; rear lift gate failure; rapid deceleration while using adaptive cruise control; increased braking distance; harder steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of ADAS can cause unintended steering wheel movement, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when encountering bicyclists, motorcycles, or other vehicles.
symptoms: Unintended steering wheel movement; lane departure warning flashes; steering pulls the vehicle towards oncoming traffic or obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column Noise and Potential Safety Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clicking noise coming from the steering column area can pose an unknown danger to occupants and bystanders, potentially indicating a more serious underlying issue.
symptoms: Clicking noise from the steering column area after driving on the highway for approximately 15 minutes; noise can be heard at low speeds or when turning the steering wheel while parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Hesitation and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation and loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to accelerate, leading to potential accidents, especially when entering traffic or merging.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates when accelerating from a stop or standstill
the vehicle hesitates when trying to accelerate in normal mode
the vehicle hesitates when trying to slow down
the transmission seems to not be shifting properly
the vehicle loses power to all wheels
the RPMs increase without corresponding acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AWD system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to potential accidents, especially in inclement weather or slippery road conditions.
symptoms: The warning light comes on indicating a problem with the AWD system
the vehicle loses power to all wheels
the vehicle only powers the front wheels.
